                <head>241. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 20, the French and Tunisian Governments concluded a Protocol of
                    Agreement recognizing Tunisian independence. United States recognition was
                    extended on March 22. For text of a message of that date from Consul General
                    Morris N. Hughes to the Bey of Tunis, see <hi rend="italic">American Foreign
                        Policy: Current Documents, 1956</hi>, page 726. The text of a message of the
                    same date from Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Douglas Dillon</persName>
                    to the French Foreign Ministry is <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
